---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="GovCompass is a free political education project making South Africa's governance, economy, safety, and human development legible to ordinary citizens."
>
  <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-6">
    About GovCompass
  </h1>

  <div class="space-y-6 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      GovCompass is a free, long-form political education project for South
      Africa. It started with a simple question: why is it so hard for an
      engaged citizen to understand how the country actually works? Not the
      party politics — the systems underneath. How money flows from Treasury
      to your town. Why the police solve so few cases. What drives economic
      growth and what blocks it. Why health and education outcomes lag behind
      what our spending should deliver.
    </p>

    <p>
      The result is a structured series of over fifty articles spanning four
      interconnected topics: <strong class="text-text-primary">Government
      Structure</strong>, <strong class="text-text-primary">Safety &
      Security</strong>, <strong class="text-text-primary">Economic
      Growth</strong>, and <strong class="text-text-primary">Human
      Development</strong>. Together they map the reinforcing cycle that
      connects governance quality to lived outcomes — and show where that
      cycle is broken.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Who this is for
    </h2>

    <p>
      GovCompass is written for the "missing middle" — people who are
      educated, engaged, and frustrated, but were never taught how the system
      actually works. You vote, you pay tax, you read the news, but the gap
      between headline outrage and structural understanding remains wide. We
      aim to close that gap.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Editorial principles
    </h2>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Non-partisan:</strong> GovCompass
        explains systems, not parties. We don't tell you who to vote for — we
        help you understand what you're voting for.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Evidence-based:</strong> Every claim
        is backed by publicly available data — from the Auditor-General and
        National Treasury to the UNDP Human Development Reports and the
        Harvard Growth Lab's economic complexity data.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Structurally focused:</strong> We
        diagnose systems, not symptoms. Each topic traces root causes, maps
        institutional design, and identifies where reforms have leverage.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Accessible:</strong> Written for
        smart people who aren't specialists. No jargon without explanation, no
        assumptions about prior knowledge.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Free:</strong> All content is free
        and always will be. No paywall, no premium tier, no ads.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Methodology
    </h2>

    <p>
      Each article follows a consistent methodology. We start with the
      constitutional and legislative framework — what the law says should
      happen. We then layer on institutional analysis — what actually happens
      and why. We use official data to quantify the gap between design and
      reality, draw on international comparators to show what is possible,
      and end with practical takeaways for citizens.
    </p>

    <p>
      Where we propose reforms — particularly in the Safety & Security and
      Economic Growth series — we ground them in evidence from countries that
      have faced similar challenges. We sequence proposals by institutional
      prerequisites, estimate fiscal costs where data permits, and identify
      the political economy constraints that make implementation hard.
    </p>

    <p>
      Sources are cited throughout and collected in our
      <a
        href="/data-sources"
        class="text-compass-green underline hover:text-opacity-80"
      >
        Data Sources
      </a> page. We draw on official government publications, audited
      financial data, international development indices, academic research,
      and independent civil society analysis — never unnamed sources or
      speculation.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Contact
    </h2>

    <p>
      Questions, corrections, or suggestions? Reach out at
      <strong class="text-text-primary">hello@govcompass.co.za</strong>.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
